<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="547" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,690,1366]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1269,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,432,1269,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,339,1270,1293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[354,432,1269,1293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">lactata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[439,529,1269,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[439,529,1269,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the aedeagal shaft similar to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[985,1104,1270,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[985,1002,1270,1293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1017,1104,1270,1293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">micrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1111,1202,1269,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1111,1202,1269,1294]" pageId="6" pageNumber="547">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see below), but can be distinguished from the latter by the face being yellowish-white and scutellum light yellow, and the aedeagus broadened subapically and compressed subbasally in ventral view.
</paragraph>
